{{Infobox person | name = Ibn Ghazi al-Miknasi | birth_date = 1437 | birth_place = [[Meknes]] | death_place = 1513 }}{{Moroccan literature}} '''Abu Abdallah Muhammad b. Ahmad b. Muhammad Ibn Ghazi al-'Utmani al-Miknasi''' (1437&ndash;1513) was a [[Morocco|Moroccan]] scholar in the field of [[history]], [[Sharia|Islamic law]], [[Arabic]] [[philology]] and [[mathematics]]. He was born in [[Meknes]] from banu uthman, a clan in the [[Berbers|Berber]] [[kutama]] tribe,<ref>{{Cite book|url=|title=Les historiens des Chorfa; essai sur la littérature historique et biographique au Maroc du XVIe au XXe siècle|last=Lévi-Provençal|first=Evariste|date=|publisher=Paris E. Larose|year=1922|isbn=|location=|page=225|pages=|quote=|author-link=Évariste Lévi-Provençal|via=}}</ref> but spent his life in [[Fes|Fez]].<ref>[[Évariste Lévi-Provençal]], ''Les Historiens du Chorfa, Essai sur la littérature historique et biographique au Maroc, du XVIe au XXe siècle'', (1922), pp. 224&ndash;30</ref> Ibn Ghazi wrote a three-volume history of Meknes and a commentary to the treatise of [[Ibn al-Banna]], ''Munyat al-hussab''. For an explanation of his work, Ibn Ghazi wrote another treatise (about 300 pages long) titled ''Bughyat al-tulab fi sharh munyat al-hussab'' ("The desire of students for an explanation of the calculator's craving"). He included sections on arithmetic and algebraic methods. He is also the author of ''Kulliyat'', a short work on legal questions and judgements in the Maliki madhab.<ref>E. Levi-Provencal, Chorfa, p. 231</ref>
==References== {{reflist}}
