'''''Tsar Maximilian''''' ({{lang-ru|Царь Максимилиан}}) is a well-known and complex [[Russian folklore|Russian folk]] [[theatre]], having enjoyed wide popularity throughout [[European Russia]] from the 18th to the early 20th century.<ref>Warner, Lisa. [https://www.jstor.org/stable/1260435 The Role of Folk-Songs in the Russian Folk-Plays]. ''Folklore'', Vol. 84, No. 1 (Spring, 1973), pp. 38-50</ref><ref>Warner, Lisa. [https://www.jstor.org/stable/1258401 The Russian Folk Play 'Tsar Maximillian': An Examination of Some Possible Origins and Sources]. ''Folklore'', Vol. 82, No. 3 (Autumn, 1971), pp. 185-206</ref>

